Austrian Stocks: Andritz, Erste Bank, RHI, Zumtobel Move

-- B y   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 
2011-03-08T16:50:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/austrian-stocks-andritz-erste-rhi-zumtobel-move-in-vienna.html
Austria’s benchmark ATX Index
dropped 0.3 percent to 2,824.57 at the close in Vienna.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Austrian market. Symbols are in parentheses.  Andritz AG (ANDR AV) jumped 4.6 percent to 64.38 euros,
ending a two-day loss, as the maker of machines for the paper
and steel industries posted a full-year net income that beat
analyst estimates and said it is expecting 2011 sales to
“increase substantially compared to 2010” and net income to
rise.    Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)  , Eastern  Europe ’s second-
biggest lender, slid 1 percent to 35.92 euros. Citigroup Inc.
cut its recommendation to “hold” from “buy.”    RHI AG (RHI)   lost 4 percent to 25.45 euros, falling for
a fifth day. The maker of fireproof materials said fourth-
quarter net income fell 10 percent to 15.2 million euros as tax
charges and its losses from financial instruments rose.  The company will pay its first dividend since it scrapped
the payout for the 2001 business year.    Zumtobel AG (ZAG)   rose 5 percent to 23.74 euros, after
climbing 6.3 percent yesterday. Europe’s biggest maker of
industrial lighting had its price estimate lifted to 27 euros at
Deutsche Bank AG and to 24 euros at HSBC Holdings Plc. The
company yesterday reported third-quarter earnings that were
twice as high as those estimated by analysts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francesca Cinelli in Milan at 
 fcinelli@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net . 